servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Peel and cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top
rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}(trimmed and sliced) and
@Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and sliced) into rounds. Peel and mince or grate
@ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine radishes, cucumber, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp},
@sugar{1%tsp}, a pinch of salt and pepper, and a pinch of ginger to taste. Set
aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @sesame oil{1%tbsp}. Add
@shredded red cabbage{4%oz}; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. In a
#small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} and @sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Add
water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with salt and pepper.

Once sweet potatoes are roasted, carefully toss with @soy sauce{2%tbsp},
@honey{2%tsp}, and half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later).
Return to oven until glazed and shiny, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Divide sweet potatoes between tortillas. Top with
sesame slaw and pickled veggies (discarding pickling liquid). Drizzle with
sriracha crema. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds to taste.

> What are sweet potatoes doing in a taco, you ask? These tasty tubers are the
perfect way to make taco night meatless!

> With the help of some seriously satisfying toppings—ginger-pickled radish and
cucumber, sesame cabbage slaw, and sriracha crema—this recipe packs everything
you could ever want inside steamy tortillas.